The paper deals with machine learning algorithms (inverse reinforcement learning and reinforcement learning) and their application to human performance feedback interventions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and robotics (RO) as it tests the algorithms on human participants and discusses potential applications in robotics. Additionally, the paper discusses modifications to reward functions to improve human feedback interventions, which falls under the sub-category of social and information sciences (SI). Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (AI) as it deals with algorithms that learn from human behavior.
